===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|Baioarii||Bavarians}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|Bojuvarii}}, literally, "[[Boii]] settlers", compound of {{etyl|cel-gau|en}} {{m|cel-gau|Boii||the Boii tribe}} and {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*warjaz||settler}} (compare {{cog|non|verjar||defender, settler}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} (compare {{cog|cy|gwerin||crowd}}, {{cog|sa|वृन्द||group, troop, crowd|tr=vṛndá}}). This name was adopted by the [[Marcomanni]] after defeating the Boii and settling [[Bohemia]] and parts of Bavaria.

